    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nI am familiar with nvim-lspconfig's [autostart functionality](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/76e7c8b029e6517f3689390d6599e9b446551704/lua/lspconfig/configs.lua#L99-L113). I find it odd that there's no corresponding auto*stop* functionality. If I manually change the filetype of a buffer, I see a new LSP server start up, but the old one is still running.\r\n\r\nI found this Reddit thread sort of talking about this: https://www.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/15h6f4o/lsp_is_started_even_though_i_change_the_filetype/, but I haven't been able to find any discussion here or over on neovim core.\r\n\r\nIs this a feature you're open to adding to nvim-lspconfig? If so, I'd be happy to send in a PR implementing it!",
